1.6 More complex data
For the most part, I find myself working with 2D structured data (i.e., table with rows and columns). But sometimes, when you are working with complex experimental designs (e.g., multiple factors) it can be useful to try nesting your data.






Letâ€™s use the ChickWeight data as a quick example




dat &lt;- ChickWeight |&gt; 
  janitor::clean_names() |&gt; 
  as_tibble()

dat |&gt;
  glimpse()

Rows: 578
Columns: 4
